===Etymology===
{{PIE root|en|gʰreh₁}}
From {{etyl|enm|en}} {{m|enm|growen}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{m|ang|grōwan||to grow, increase, flourish, germinate}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*grōaną||to grow, grow green}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*gʰreh₁-||to grow, become green}}.
{{rel-top|cognates}}
Cognate with {{cog|sco|grow}}, {{m|sco|grew||to grow}}, {{cog|frr|grojen}}, {{m|frr|growen||to grow}}, {{cog|fy|groeie||to grow}}, Dutch {{m|nl|groeien||to grow}}, German Low German {{m|nds-de|grojen||to green; thrive; take hold; flourish}}, {{cog|gmh|grüejen||to grow, grow green}}, {{cog|da|gro||to grow}}, {{cog|no|gro||to grow}}, {{cog|sv|gro||to germinate, grow, sprout}}, {{cog|is|gróa||to grow}}, {{cog|la|herba||plant, herb, weed}}, {{cog|sv|gröda||crop}}, {{cog|frr|greyde||growth, pasture}}. Related to [[growth]], [[grass]], [[green]].
